Anyone ever experienced not feeling as smart as they used to feel? I know there are several external factors for this, im just wondering how did you overcame it
Xyra
@XyraSinclair
brain is constantly adapting to environment and adaptions happen at various rates. staying healthy, psychically diverse (changing environment, giving opportunities for different stories to be told), staying close to high potentia and what excites you (being adequately courageous!), staying hungry and raw at least sometimes (e.g. no sugar, no nutting, eschewing X questionable habit, sometimes no calories) taps into the brain's survivable network.

I went from being somewhat of a degen short form addict to prompting all the time and tapping into my gut again, feeling and embracing the raw survival stress that is being a human.

don't sweat temporary lost in capabilities like suddenly being shit at some manual coding, skills generally come back if they are necessary. IME brains have a remarkable ability to prioritize beyond what one thinks they should prioritize.

we have a little server that aint doing much. it could probably host this additionally for qwern.net. draft up a full  complete spec, that works friendly with caddy. current caddyfile is: aiabusehotline.org {
    encode gzip

    # Security headers
    header {
        # Prevent clickjacking
        X-Frame-Options DENY

        # Prevent MIME type sniffing
        X-Content-Type-Options nosniff

        # XSS protection (legacy, but harmless)
        X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block"

        # Force HTTPS
        Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload"

        # Control referrer information
        Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin"

        # Content Security Policy - restrictive but allows inline styles for the simple UI
        Content-Security-Policy "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'"

        # Disable various browser features we don't need
        Permissions-Policy "accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()"

        # Prevent cross-origin isolation attacks
        Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy "same-origin"
        Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy "same-origin"
    }

    # API routes -> Bun
    handle /api/* {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3000
    }

    # Web form submissions -> Bun
    handle /web/* {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3000
    }

    # Admin API -> Bun
    handle /admin/* {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3000
    }

    # Internal admin panel -> Bun
    handle /internal/* {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3000
    }

    # Health check
    handle /health {
        reverse_proxy localhost:3000
    }

    # Static files
    handle {
        root * /opt/aiabusehotline/static
        file_server
    }

    log {
        output file /var/log/caddy/aiabusehotline.log
    }
}

